How to install jekyll in Ubuntu?
1. install ruby:  
      sudo apt-get install ruby
2. install ruby-devel:
      sudo apt-get install ruby-all-dev
3. install jekyll
      sudo gem install --http-proxy https://ip:port jekyll
4. install bundler
      sudo gem install --http-proxy https://ip:port bundler
5. install minima
      sudo gem install --http-proxy https://ip:port minima


